                    <div class="endpoint-name">/pokemon</div>
                    <div class="endpoint-desc">Complete Pokémon information including stats, abilities, moves, types, and sprites. The core endpoint for individual Pokémon data.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint-card">
                    <div class="endpoint-name">/pokemon-species</div>
                    <div class="endpoint-desc">Species-specific data including evolution chains, flavor text entries, genus information, and regional variants.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint-card">
                    <div class="endpoint-name">/pokemon-form</div>
                    <div class="endpoint-desc">Different forms of Pokémon such as Alolan forms, Mega evolutions, and regional variants with specific sprites.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint-card">
                    <div class="endpoint-name">/pokemon-color</div>
                    <div class="endpoint-desc">Color classifications for Pokémon used in Pokédex entries and game mechanics.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint-card">
                    <div class="endpoint-name">/pokemon-shape</div>
                    <div class="endpoint-desc">Body shape categories that group Pokémon by their physical appearance structure.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint-card">
                    <div class="endpoint-name">/pokemon-habitat</div>
                    <div class="endpoint-desc">Natural habitat classifications where Pokémon can typically be found in the wild.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
